message: First, use 'filter' on all liquids and gases (they become 'liquid, filtered'). Use 'vial' on all solids (they become 'liquid, extracted'). Both tools convert items to value 30. message: Always use the 'vial' tool to extract solids into liquids first. Combining two *extracted* items with similar themes (e.g., two magical liquids, two mundane liquids) generally yields a valuable item (around 60 points). Filtering items usually results in 'poorly-filtered' items and lowers their value, so generally avoid it. Combining more than two items, or combining items that already have 'botched' or 'poorly-filtered' features, often leads to significantly negative values. Also, using 'vial' on gas items seems to result in 'failed extraction' and negative value. If a specific combination is hinted at (like basilisk + batwing), definitely try it, as these can yield very high values (around 70) even if themes are mixed, but ensure ingredients are in liquid/extract form. When you have a good score (60+), consider submitting.
